<xmi:XMI xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1">
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:ProcessDescription xmi:id="--5knk7ISjEg6uXYfRkzlLA" name="Preparation for runtime monitoring of trust and trustworthiness,_p9CQ0RxNEeOF_P09ig5mEw" guid="--5knk7ISjEg6uXYfRkzlLA">
    <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This activity is carried out during the design and development time of the system. The system designer/developer uses&#xD;
    this capability to create interfaces which are accessible by the runtime monitoring and management functions. To this&#xD;
    end, the following inputs are used:&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Lists of threats and associated controls per asset&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For each asset, an interface is defined which exposes the values of the trust or trustworthiness properties. These&#xD;
    properties can be seen as indicators of trustworthiness at runtime. For each threat, a set of symptoms is defined, and&#xD;
    the designer provides interfaces for the observation of trustworthiness properties that will be used to identify these&#xD;
    symptoms at runtime. For each control, the designer defines asset-specific mechanisms, and provides an interface to the&#xD;
    management subsystem to actually invoke the control.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
    <keyConsiderations>&lt;span&#xD;
style='FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA'>&#xD;
The staff performing this activity must be aware of how the trustworthiness maintenance (i.e., monitoring and management)&#xD;
is carried out at runtime, so that the designed interfaces are useful for the chosen trustworthiness maintenance&#xD;
approach.&lt;/span></keyConsiderations>
    <purpose>&lt;span&#xD;
style='FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: IT; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA'>&#xD;
The system should facilitate the monitoring of trust and trustworthiness by providing methods for the runtime&#xD;
trustworthiness maintenance to gather values of trustworthiness properties, which indicate threat activity, observe the&#xD;
events in the running system, and activate the controls to mitigate the threats.&lt;/span></purpose>
    <howtoStaff>The staff performing this activity must part of the design and development team.</howtoStaff>
    <scope>design and development time</scope>
    <usageNotes>During design and development time, the capability pattern must beis used to enable trust and trustworthiness measurement&#xD;
monitoring and management at runtime, so that the trustworthiness maintenance system can analyse and react on&#xD;
trustworthiness losses. &lt;br />&#xD;
If new assets, threats, or controls are identified at runtime, this capability is needed to reconfigure the monitoring and&#xD;
management system.&lt;br /></usageNotes>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:ProcessDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-klNuegg9DB1mS0gB1AsMWg" name="Design Observation and Control Interfaces,_0MfXUBxhEeOF_P09ig5mEw" guid="-klNuegg9DB1mS0gB1AsMWg">
    <keyConsiderations>&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        There may be more than one control that can be activated for a particular threat&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The observation of threat activity may only be possible by indirect observation of asset properties. In some cases&#xD;
        the cause of the threat may be external to the STS, and thus not directly observable.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Trust beliefs may likewise be hard to observe directly.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></keyConsiderations>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-jelG1ZgPxpZ8Xs1p-k-eNw" name="System Trust and Trustworthiness Architect,_0Mf-YBxhEeOF_P09ig5mEw" guid="-jelG1ZgPxpZ8Xs1p-k-eNw">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The person in this role is primarily responsible for the following tasks:&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Design the Observation and Management interfaces for each asset in the STS&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Create the System Trust and Trustworthiness Observation and Management Interface document&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Ensure that the interfaces are implemented by the system developers&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-4V1Jff_VkIEHI6sgAxH6PQ" name="Implement Observation and Control Interfaces,_2aqfEBxhEeOF_P09ig5mEw" guid="-4V1Jff_VkIEHI6sgAxH6PQ">
    <refinedDescription>This task is a standard task in software engineering:</refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-ofaDYaVSP0l6nwSLIqow6A" name="System Developer,_2aqfERxhEeOF_P09ig5mEw" guid="-ofaDYaVSP0l6nwSLIqow6A">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The person in this role is primarily responsible for the following tasks:&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Implement the Observation and Management interfaces for each asset in the STS&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Test the interfaces&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
